<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph'><span
lang=EN-US style='font-size:14.0pt;font-family:"Calibri","sans-serif"'>Hello
everyone ,</span><span lang=EN-US><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph'><span
lang=EN-US style='font-size:14.0pt;font-family:"Calibri","sans-serif"'>&nbsp;</span><span
lang=EN-US><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph'><span
lang=EN-US style='font-size:14.0pt;font-family:"Calibri","sans-serif"'>For the
purpose to migrate the OpenMPI to VxWorks ,I have set up a VxWorks development
environment with WorkBench 3.0. It is really a good news that the WorkBench
supports gnu building tools, bash and some frequently used command like sed
,awd and so on but not the Autotools (Autoconf/Automake) .Once I wonder the
configure script file generated under the linux may work well under the
workbench shell environment . But it is a frustrate to find when I launch the
configure ,it just hang without any prompt .I look into the problem and found
maybe the version of the bash in the VxWorks is too low to parse the configure
file .</span><span lang=EN-US><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph'><span
lang=EN-US style='font-size:14.0pt;font-family:"Calibri","sans-serif"'>Then I
come across the cmake which is used to as building tools under windows for the
openmpi. Because of the feature of “cross-platform” ,I think it is possible to
use cmake to migrate .Also I found boostcmake project which supports the
vxworks gnu compile tools using cmake .</span><span lang=EN-US><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph'><span
lang=EN-US style='font-size:14.0pt;font-family:"Calibri","sans-serif"'>But
considering my poor knowledge about the building system (Autotools,cmake,etc),I
need some guide and advice to review what I plan to do is a possible .</span><span
lang=EN-US><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph'><span
lang=EN-US style='font-size:14.0pt;font-family:"Calibri","sans-serif"'>&nbsp;</span><span
lang=EN-US><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph'><span
lang=EN-US style='font-size:14.0pt;font-family:"Calibri","sans-serif"'>Thank
you in advance !</span><span lang=EN-US><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph'><span
